This course is a continuation of CHEM-053, General Chemistry Laboratory I, and has a co-requisite course of Chemistry 102. If a student withdraws from or drops a co-requisite course, he/she must also withdraw from or drop the laboratory course. There is a $150 lab fee for CHEM-054. &#8232;&#8232;

Students generally found the course content to be “hand-in-hand with that of CHEM-102”. The lab helped students to review the material and concepts from lecture; however, most students did not find the lab course to be too valuable a learning experience. &#8232;&#8232;

Professor Philips received a great deal of praise for being very communicative and embodying “the trifecta of desirable professor qualities – kindness, brilliance and wit.” There were, however, quite a few complaints regarding her use of “clickers.” &#8232;&#8232;

Students generally found the course content challenging, and thought both the midterm and final were harder than expected. Some students found the workload to be unnecessarily tedious, and felt that they could have grasped concepts with much shorter experiment times.

